element.name: Old Shilleaghs by Windsockers, Traditional Cache (1.5/1.5)

long-description.p:
As far back as the late 1800’s a GAA team has been playing on the Donabate peninsula back then the team was known as ‘The Old Shilleaghs’.
Modern history of the club began in 1924 with the establishment of the Fingal League and the club was renamed St. Patrick’s GAA Club. League wins for the club are recorded as far back as 1932 and history shows that the 30’s were a successful time for the club. But you don’t have to go back that far for club successes at St. Pat’s. Dublin Junior Championship 1980, Dublin Minor Champions 1991, AFL Div. 6 Champions 2006, Under 21 Champions 2007 and reigning Dublin Minor Champions Div.5. Dublin Junior Championship 2008 and runners-up AFL 5 2008 has brought promotion for the First Senior Team to AFL Division 4, with the Second Senior Team also being promoted to AFL Div. 10.Looking forward is what St. Patrick’s GAA Club is all about. It is a thriving club, fielding twelve teams catering for boys, girls and means football. There is also a very active Nursery section for 4-8 year old boys and girls to learn and develop their skills in a fun environment. A “Street League” is run every year, with over two hundred children participating. The league finishes off with the Street League final and a family fun day which last summer brought in over a thousand participants and spectators.

The Cache is a micro container.
Please take care and rehide the cache to prevent muggles from
discovering its location.
